{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Require free subscriptions stop after trial & do not take bank details upfront",
        "additional_details": "It is very common for digital subscriptions (music, video, digital services) to require our payment details upfront despite being advertised as free to try. These types of trial subscriptions are then very often automatically converted to recurring subscriptions after the initial trial under what we call \"act to cancel\" scheme.\r\n\r\nWe believe this mechanism is predatory and should be stopped.",
        "background": "We would like to ask the government to mandate that all free to try subscriptions must not request payment details upfront and that they should terminate at the end of the free term unless the user makes a conscious decision to convert to a full plan - \"act to keep going\", not \"act to cancel\".",
